letting it go over your head hi im a female bus driver and l work on one bad route i got threatened lastnight and also someone handed in a knife which is all too common on this route it can be very intimidating but you have to act like you dont give a shite and act tough but l find this very hard anyone any suggestions on how to let things just go over your head serious replies only please i consider myself to be polite and kind to my passengers i try and make them as comfortable as poss try not to miss stops but sometimes it happens but even so we dont deserve the abuse that we get when you have been there a bit you can move on to the better routes and let the newbies do the bad ones Shit Bus stop Newbie Sin City Knife Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Kasparov versus The World Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Subtle Knife Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Poker jargon Abu Ghraib torture and prisoner abuse The Inside Domestic violence Shaggy dog story Milton H. Erickson 2000 Australian Grand Prix YuYu Hakusho Bus rapid transit Social rule Internet troll Transport in Hong Kong Bulk vending Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Kowloon Motor Bus Rosa Parks Taxi Driver Meat Loaf Toronto Transit Commission Humphrey Bogart Piccolo Junior Saga The Amber Spyglass London Buses Bus Pip (South Park episode) Wyatt Earp Whose Line Is It Anyway? Speed limit New York City Subway Volvo B10TL Routemaster Ottawa O-Train 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Colony in Space The Adventures of Pete & Pete Hey Jude Khatushyamji RuneScape quests Pattaya Montgomery Bus Boycott Rape Nicomachean Ethics Brihanmumbai Electric Supply and Transport Public transport Sail training James Hanratty The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Motorola 68000 Train Tenshinhan Freedom Riders Public light bus Maverick (film) The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Bulldozer Southeastern Pennsylvania Transportation Authority Personal rapid transit Women in Islam Free will Alcoholics Anonymous CPU cach